\frametitle{In R Statistics}
  In R Statistics, you can find the confidence interval for the slope
  of the regression line as follows,
\begin{alltt}
confint(lm(faithful[[2]]~faithful[[1]]),'faithful[[1]]',level=0.95)
\end{alltt}
